para_trans: Forest Land-Pune

Diversion of 0.3312 ha of Reserved Forest land in favour of Lonavala Municipal Council, Lonavala for construction of road passing through Forest Survey No. 57 of Village- Bhushi, Taluka- Maval, District- Pune in the State of Maharashtra.
Government of Maharashtra
Revenue and Forest Department
Government Order No.FLD-2021/C.R.215/F-10
Mantralaya, Mumbai 400032.
Reference:
1) Additional Principal Chief Conservator of Forests & Nodal Officer, Letter No.
2) Integrated Regional Office, Ministry of Environment, Forests & Climate Change, Government of India, Nagpur Letter No.FC-I/MH-247/2021-NGP/9106, dt.
3) Additional Principal Chief Conservator of Forests & Nodal Officer, Letter No.
4) Integrated Regional Office, Ministry of Environment, Forests & Climate Change, Government of India, Nagpur Letter No.FC-I/MH-247/2021-NGP/10620, dt.
5) Additional Principal Chief Conservator of Forests & Nodal Officer, Letter No.
Order:-
Whereas, the Additional Principal Chief Conservator of Forests & Nodal Officer,
Nagpur vide letter under reference No.1 has submitted a proposal to The Deputy Director
General (Central), Ministry of Environment, Forests & Climate Change, Regional Office,
Government of India, Nagpur for diversion of 0.3312 ha of Reserved Forest land in favour
of Lonavala Municipal Council, Lonavala for construction of road passing through Forest
Survey No. 57 of Village- Bhushi, Taluka- Maval, District- Pune in the State of
Maharashtra;
AND whereas, the Government of India after due consideration, vide letter under
Reference No.2, accorded 'In-principle' approval to divert the 0.3312 ha. The Forest Land for
the above project under section 2 of Van (Sanrakshan Evam Samvardhan) Adhiniyam,
1980. The said approval is subject to fulfillment of certain conditions by the User Agency;
Government Order No. FLD-2021/C.R.215/F-10
AND whereas, the Additional Principal Chief Conservator of Forests & Nodal
Officer, Maharashtra State, Nagpur vide letters under reference No.3 has submitted
compliance of those conditions to the Government of India;
AND whereas, the Integrated Regional Office, Ministry of Environment, Forests &
Climate Change, Government of India, Nagpur, wide under reference no. 4 Accorded 'Final
Approval 'to divert the of 0.3312 ha of Reserved Forest Land in preference of Lonavala
Municipal Council, Lonavala for construction of road passing through Forest Survey No.
57 of Village- Bhushi, Taluka- Maval, District- Pune in the State of Maharashtra under
section 2 of Van (Sanrakshan Evam Samvardhan) Adhiniyam, 1980;
AND whereas, the Additional Principal Chief Conservator of Forests & Nodal
Officer, Maharashtra State, Nagpur vide letter under reference No.5 has requested State
Government to issue diversion order in the matter;
NOW, therefore, Government of Maharashtra hereby directs that the area of 0.3312
ha. consisting of Reserved Forest Land more specifically described in the proposal
submitted vide letter under reference No. | and as per details given in the Schedule given
below, be diverted to the User Agency, 1.e. Chief Officer, Lonavala Municipal Council,
Lonavala for construction of road passing through Forest Survey No. 57 of Village- Bhushi,
Taluka- Maval, District- Pune in the State of Maharashtra.
The diversion shall be effected subject to the terms and conditions mentioned in the
letters dated 31.12.2021 and dated 22.11.2022 of Integrated Regional Office, MOEF&CC,
Nagpur. This approval for diversion of forest land is also subject to compliance of
following conditions by the User Agency-
The User Agency shall comply with all the conditions stipulated in the '1in-principle'.
and 'final approval' letters of Integrated Regional Office, MoEF & CC, Nagpur,
referred above. The Chief Conservator of Forests (T), Pune shall ensure the strict
compliance of the conditions by the User Agency and shall furnish the report in this
regard to Additional Principal Chief Conservator of Forests and Nodal Officer,
Maharashtra State, Nagpur from time to time.
2. For ensuring the compliances and for monitoring the duly prescribed activities and
also to carry out other statuary duties, user agency shall facilitate unhindered access/entry in the area to the local forest Officer. In case the user agency prohibits
the free access or create hindrances, the permission given under this Order for the
diversion of forest area for the non-forest use shall be withdrawn.
3. Non-compliance of any of the conditions mentioned in Integrated Regional Office, MoEF&CC letters dated 31.12.2021 and dated 22.11.2022, in this order and Rules
& Guidelines made / issued under Van (Sanrakshan Evam Samvardhan)
Adhiniyam, 1980, shall amount to violation of Van (Sanrakshan Evam Samvardhan)
Adhiniyam, 1980 and action would be taken accordingly.
Government Order No. FLD-2021/C.R.215/F-10
4. In case of non-compliance of any of the above conditions, the Chief Conservator of
Forests (T), Pune shall report through the State Government to the Integrated
Regional Officer (Central), Ministry of Environment, Forests & Climate Change,
Government of India, Nagpur as per procedure laid down in guidelines under the
Van (Sanrakshan Evam Samvardhan) Adhiniyam, 1980.
SCHEDULE
